@6044:
It is a truth universally acknowledged that gays give the best bjs. 
K, with that said I've given plenty of straight guys in my building a little action when I lived on campus. Dw tho, I'm sure your "straightness'" is intact lmao.

@6166

i can empathize

I didn't know how touch-starved I really was until I came to uni. My friends are all pretty amicable people who're comfortable with friendly hugs and touches, but like, sometimes I crave more? I'm not even looking for a relationship or a fwb, but literally someone who could hang out with me to do hw and then afterwards we cuddle next to each other before falling asleep, but my roomies and friends were rlly skeptical of that and were like, "Uhhh u can't just be comfy with a stranger that you don't know at all, dude." So I kinda understand what 6166 means. It kinda sucks when you have rlly nice girl friends who aren't afraid to show affection to you, but you're looking for sth more intimate (but... just not too intimate).

@OP 6614
SPEW is a terrible example of trying to convince us that Hermione is black. She could easily be a "white abolitionist." In the wizarding world house elves actually want to serve their masters (unless they were mistreated, and that was not the mission of SPEW). The elves that worked at Hogwarts refused to clean up the clothes set up to "free" them because they were truly happier working for the school. 
This, of course, is nothing like the real world, where all humans should enjoy freedom and equal opportunity.
